description: Alteration of earlier scunch (“back part of the side of an opening”), short for scuncheon.

entries.meaning: (architecture) A structure constructed between two adjacent walls to aid in the transition from a polygonal to a circular structure, as when a dome is constructed on top of a square room.

description: Uncertain. Probably blend of squint +‎ pinch. Compare squink-eyed, variant of squint-eyed, so perhaps it is at least partly an altered form of squint.

verbs.description: squinch (third-person singular simple present squinches, present participle squinching, simple past and past participle squinched)
